        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 27 at 2:47PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Benton, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Benton, Conasauga, Big Frog Mountain, and Parksville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
